## CROSS-PLATFORM TESTING

For testing across multiple platforms:

1. DESIGN tests that run on all platforms:
   - Use platform-agnostic APIs where possible
   - Implement platform-specific test variations when needed
   - Use conditional compilation for platform-specific tests
   - Test on all target platforms regularly

2. TEST platform-specific features:
   - Create dedicated tests for each platform
   - Verify platform abstraction correctness
   - Check for inconsistencies between platforms
   - Test platform detection logic

3. AUTOMATE cross-platform testing:
   - Configure CI to test on all platforms
   - Use matrix builds to cover platform combinations
   - Report platform-specific test results clearly
   - Prioritize fixing cross-platform issues

ONE SOLUTION ONLY:
```rust
// Cross-platform testing pattern
#[cfg(test)]
mod platform_tests {
    use super::*;
    
    // Common test that should work on all platforms
    #[test]
    fn test_core_algorithm_all_platforms() {
        let input = create_test_input();
        let result = process_data(&input);
        assert_eq!(result.value, 42);
    }
    
    // Platform-specific tests
    #[cfg(target_arch = "wasm32")]
    mod web_tests {
        use super::*;
        
        #[test]
        fn test_web_specific_feature() {
            let result = initialize_web_renderer();
            assert!(result.is_ok());
        }
    }
    
    #[cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))]
    mod native_tests {
        use super::*;
        
        #[test]
        fn test_native_specific_feature() {
            let result = initialize_native_renderer();
            assert!(result.is_ok());
        }
    }
}
```

